menu "breadboard: bb_log_event"

config BB_LOG_EVENT_AUTO_ATTACH
    bool "Auto-attach 'log' bb_event stream topic to /api/events"
    default y
    help
        When enabled (default), bb_log_event registers a non-retained "log"
        bb_event stream topic and attaches it to /api/events at regular-tier
        order 4. This is THE primary log transport — structured JSON served
        at GET /api/events?topic=log; the legacy /api/logs raw-text SSE
        route has been retired.

        Each log line is forwarded as structured JSON:
        {"ts":<ms>,"level":"I|W|E|D|V|?","tag":"<tag>","msg":"<text>"}

        The forwarder feeds from a dedicated queue (see BB_LOG_EVENT_QUEUE_LEN)
        inside bb_log's s_log_vprintf so the hot logging path is never blocked.

        Disable only if you want the log topic available to direct bb_event
        subscribers without surfacing it on /api/events.

config BB_LOG_EVENT_QUEUE_LEN
    int "Log event forwarder queue depth"
    default 48 if SPIRAM
    default 24
    range 8 256
    depends on BB_LOG_EVENT_AUTO_ATTACH
    help
        Number of slots in the off-hot-path forwarder queue between
        bb_log's s_log_vprintf and the bb_log_event forwarder task. Each slot
        holds one log line (~192 B), so 48 slots ~ 9 KB worst-case buffering.
        Lines are dropped (with a counter) when the queue is full; the
        dropped count is visible via bb_log_event_dropped().

        PSRAM-axis DERIVE: default 48 on SPIRAM boards (ample heap); 24 on
        no-PSRAM boards (~4.6 KB, lower than the prior 48-slot default that
        allocated ~9 KB on heap-tight boards). Per-board sdkconfig fragments
        (e.g. esp32-s2-mini at 8) override this derive and take precedence.

endmenu
